  "texts": [
    "We formulated this question to provide insights toward three ML topics that might help tackle current challenges and open future opportunities that might prove useful in scanpath processing.",
    "The three topics are Self-supervised learning, Transformers, and Explainable AI.",
    "We start by explaining each topic and offer our opinion on how they can be utilized for scanpath processing in passive gaze-based interaction.",
    "Self-supervised learning Self-supervised learning (SSL) is an ML approach where the system learns to understand and work with data without being explicitly provided with labeled examples during training; instead, it generates its labels from the input data (Nguyen et al., 2021; Liu et al., 2023), which is achieved by designing a task where the model predicts some parts of the data using other parts of the data.",
    "SSL differs from unsupervised learning because instead of dealing with structural patterns in the data for clustering or dimensionality reduction, it focuses on solving supervised learning tasks such as classification, which can be done using multiple approaches."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Self-supervised learning Self-supervised learning (SSL) is an ML approach where the system learns to understand and work with data without being explicitly provided with labeled examples during training; instead, it generates its labels from the input data (Nguyen et al., 2021; Liu et al., 2023), which is achieved by designing a task where the model predicts some parts of the data using other parts of the data."
